==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acrania
<hw>A*cra"ni*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ skull.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Partial or total absence of the
skull.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The lowest group
of Vertebrata, including the amphioxus, in which no skull
exists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acranial</ent>⟦br⟧
